    "hadith_number": "1890",
    "english_translation": "A man from Banu Tamim said: We were with Abu al-Awwam when he recited this verse: 'Upon it are nineteen' (Surah al-Muddaththir 74:30). He asked: What do you say - is it nineteen angels or nineteen thousand angels? I said: Rather nineteen thousand. He asked: How do you know that? I said: Because Allah the Mighty and Majestic said: 'And We have not made their number except as a trial for those who disbelieve' (Surah al-Muddaththir 74:31). Abu al-Awwam said: You are right. Each angel has in his hand a mace of iron with two prongs, striking with it a strike that sends down seventy thousand demons between the shoulders of each of them a distance of...",
